qas.question: Which tribe ran the city of Nri?
When was Nri taken over by the British?
Igbo Ukwu made the oldest bronze art using which process?
Which clan is Nri in the territory of?

context: The Kingdom of Nri of the Igbo people consolidated in the 10th century and continued until it lost its sovereignty to the British in <a1_0>1911<a1_0/>. Nri was ruled by <a3_0>the Eze Nri<a3_0/>, and the city of Nri is considered to be the foundation of <a0_0>Igbo<a0_0/> culture. Nri and Aguleri, where the Igbo creation myth originates, are in the territory of the <a4_0>Umeuri<a4_0/> clan. Members of the clan trace their lineages back to the patriarchal king-figure Eri. In West Africa, the oldest bronzes made using the <a2_0>lost-wax<a2_0/> process were from Igbo Ukwu, a city under Nri influence.
